D. Acquisition Strategy
Project initially utilizes existing DoD engineering and study contracts and activities as well as new contracts (including but not limited to Small Business Innovation
Research (SBIR) and Other Transactional Agreements (OTA), which are competitively awarded, to accomplish advanced integrated mission studies. Preliminary design
studies began within the DAF Rocket Cargo Vanguard program in FY 2022. In Dec 2023 the Operational Capability Requirements Directorate (S5R) Space Mobility and
Logistics Branch was directed to develop formal P2D requirements via a Rapid Prototype Requirements Document (preliminary step to a Middle Tier Acquisition (MTA)
program).




