A. Mission Description and Budget Item Justification
The Space Systems Prototype Transitions (SSPT) Program addresses space technology and capability gaps to facilitate technology transition of military space
prototypes into programs of record. SSPT conducts an array of activities to model, integrate, test, provide launch integration for, and support on-orbit testing of prototype
technologies. The supported activities include systems engineering, technology planning, development, demonstration and testing, as well as modeling, simulation, and
exercises to support the development and maturation of tactics, techniques, and procedures (TTPs). This includes developing and prototyping critical technology within
the DoD, other government agencies, academia, and industry partners, along with the necessary systems engineering for effective deployment.

 Project 645601, Space Defense Capabilities, prototypes technologies and facilitates informed insertion to programs of record and provides platforms to operate
 prototypes in space. Project 645611, Assault Breaker II (ABII), is an all-Service, classified, multi-year effort, led by the Office of the Under Secretary of Defense for
 Research and Engineering (OUSD(R&E)) to analyze, research, and recommend material and non-material solutions to the Joint Requirements Oversight Council
 (JROC).

 The SSPT Program establishes a cost-effective framework to identify, mature and transition demonstrations and prototypes to:

 -Rapidly address identified technology or capability gaps
 -Accelerate the maturation of systems intended for demonstrations/prototypes that enhance/compliment/replace existing capabilities
 -Support a more reliable, available, maintainable, and survivable military space enterprise
 -Energize the space industrial base supporting U.S. national security
 -Focus Science and Technology (S&T) Innovation and facilitate its transition to military space programs of record

 This program element may include necessary civilian pay expenses required to manage, execute, and deliver Space Systems Prototype Transitions (SSPT) capability.
 The use of such program funds would be in addition to the civilian pay expenses budgeted in program elements 1206392SF and 1206398SF.

 This effort is in Budget Activity 4, Advanced Component Development and Prototypes (ACD&P), because efforts are necessary to evaluate integrated technologies,
 representative modes or prototype systems in a high fidelity and realistic operating environment.




