AFRL Tetra-5c has been repurposed to fulfill Tetra-6 mission.

D. Acquisition Strategy
All contracts funded in this program element will be awarded using competitive procedures to the maximum extent possible. The Space Systems Prototype Transitions
(SSPT) program consists of numerous projects in which the program office will leverage rapid prototyping authorities to the maximum extent possible.

 The Rapid On-Orbit Space Technology Evaluation Ring (ROOSTER) acquisition strategy was approved in 2Q FY 2022. A sole-source contract was awarded for
 ROOSTER 2Q FY 2023 which supports the ROOSTER-4 Initial Launch Capability (ILC) 2Q FY 2026. The follow-on ROOSTER-5 bus contract was competitively
 awarded in 1Q FY 2025 through a mission partner's contract. The payload and launch vehicle integration, ground systems development, and operation support scope
 will be awarded via sole-source contract to the bus contractor in 4Q FY 2025. The program office will develop an acquisition strategy for ROOSTER-6 in FY 2025 to
 support a contract start in late FY 2026.

 The Tetra program office maintains the flexibility to employ a different acquisition strategy to procure, develop, and launch each Tetra. The first two Tetra vehicles were
 procured simultaneously as the first award on the Space Enterprise Consortium (SpEC) Other Transaction Authority (OTA) agreement. Tetras 3 and 4 were awarded in
 4Q 2019. Tetra-5a awarded in 4Q 2022. AFRL Tetra-5c has now been re-purposed to fulfill the Tetra-6 mission which was awarded in 3Q FY 2024.


