        Change Summary Explanation
        In FY 2024, the $15.900 million decrease in Reprogrammings was to fund higher Department of the Air Force (DAF) requirements in the approved FY 2024
        Omnibus Above Threshold Reprogramming (ATR) (FY 24-11 PA).

        In FY 2025, the budget decreased by $19.300 million in Other Adjustments due to a DAF directed transfer to RDT&E, Space Force, PE 1206447SF, Resilient
        Missile Warning Missile Tracking - Medium Earth Orbit (MEO).

        The FY 2026 budget request increased by $23.745 million as a result of programmatic adjustments within the Science and Technology portfolio. This reduction
        supports a strategic realignment aimed at optimizing core research areas and enhancing resource efficiency. Main adjustments include:

        -- In FY 2026, the budget request increased by $25.000 million to accelerate Narrowband technologies, specifically 5G for tactical user equipment compatibility
        with commercial partners and LEO satellite constellations.
        -- The FY 2026 request was reduced by $0.075 million for Advisory and Assistance Services to promote efficiencies and advance the policies of the
        Administration in alignment with Executive Order 14222, "Implementing the President's Department of Government Efficiency Cost Efficiency Initiative.



